    "excerpt": "Our annual ranking of the executives, creators, and stars shaping the industry.",
    "body": "Influence in entertainment has never been more fluid. A decade ago, this list was dominated by studio heads and network executives. Today, it includes content creators with audiences larger than most cable networks, technology executives whose algorithms determine what billions of people watch, and artists whose creative decisions ripple across cultures.\n\nThis year's list reflects that evolution. The top ten includes three people who would not have appeared on this list five years ago: a streaming executive whose platform now reaches 300 million subscribers globally, a musician whose independent release strategy rewrote the rules of album distribution, and a social media creator whose production company has quietly become one of Hollywood's most prolific.\n\nThe methodology behind the list is straightforward: we measure reach (how many people are affected), revenue (economic impact), and resonance (cultural influence beyond pure numbers). Each category is weighted equally, preventing any single metric from dominating.\n\nWhat's striking about this year's rankings is the generational shift. Of the fifty names, twenty-three are under forty. Eleven are under thirty. The old guard hasn't disappeared — several veteran executives remain in the top twenty — but the centre of gravity has clearly moved.\n\n'The entertainment industry is no longer a gatekept system,' said one executive who dropped twelve places from last year. 'That's uncomfortable for people like me, but it's probably better for everyone else.'",
