    "title": "The Sequel Nobody Expected — First Look and Fan Reactions",
    "excerpt": "The franchise returns with a bold new direction. Here is everything we know so far.",
    "body": "When the original film was released seven years ago, it was conceived as a standalone story. There was no sequel clause in the contracts, no post-credits tease, no franchise blueprint. The director was explicit: this was a one-time thing.\n\nSo when the same director announced a follow-up last summer, the reaction was a mixture of excitement and apprehension. Sequels to beloved standalone films carry a particular kind of risk — the risk of diminishing something that was perfect as it was.\n\nBased on the footage we've seen and the conversations we've had with people involved in the production, this sequel is not attempting to replicate the original. It is, by all accounts, a radically different film that happens to share some characters.\n\n'The worst thing we could do is make the same film again,' the director told us. 'The characters have moved on. The world has moved on. The filmmaking should reflect that.'\n\nThe most significant change is structural. Where the original was a tightly contained thriller set over a single weekend, the sequel spans three decades and multiple continents. The tone has shifted from intimate to epic, from claustrophobic to expansive.\n\nEarly test screenings have been polarising — which the director considers a positive sign. 'If everyone likes it, we haven't done our job. This film should provoke conversation, not consensus.'\n\nThe sequel is scheduled for release in October.",
