    "title": "Celebrity Street Style: The 25 Most Iconic Looks This Month",
    "excerpt": "Off-duty fashion from the stars — casual, bold, and endlessly re-pinnable.",
    "body": "Street style photography has always occupied an interesting space in celebrity culture. Unlike red carpet images, which are managed and styled within an inch of their lives, street style captures something closer to genuine personal expression. Or at least, that's the theory.\n\nThe reality, as our photographer discovered during a month of documenting celebrity street style across New York, Los Angeles, and London, is more nuanced. Even 'casual' celebrity dressing is a performance — just a different kind of performance.\n\n'There's a calculation to it,' one stylist told us, speaking on condition of anonymity. 'When a client is photographed leaving a gym or walking to a coffee shop, they know the photos will be published. The outfit is chosen. The sunglasses are selected. The bag is positioned just so.'\n\nThat said, the best street style moments do reveal something genuine about the wearer. Our top twenty-five selections this month showcase a remarkable range: from a veteran actress whose off-duty uniform of vintage denim and plain white tees has become iconic in its simplicity, to a pop star whose experimental layering continues to push the boundaries of casual dressing.\n\nThe dominant trend this month was restraint. After years of logomania and maximalism, the most interesting looks were the quietest — neutral palettes, clean silhouettes, and investment pieces that whispered rather than shouted.\n\nFashion, it seems, is learning to breathe again.",
