    "excerpt": "From the opening bars to the hidden closer — why critics are calling it a masterpiece.",
    "body": "Three months after its release, the album continues to generate the kind of conversation usually reserved for cultural events rather than music releases. It has been dissected by academics, debated by critics, and absorbed into the cultural vocabulary of a generation.\n\nThe opening track establishes the album's thesis in under four minutes: a meditation on identity and belonging that builds from a whisper to a roar. The production — a collaboration between three of the most innovative producers working today — creates a sonic landscape that feels simultaneously intimate and vast.\n\nTrack three, which has become the album's signature song, is a masterclass in restraint. Built around a simple piano figure and a vocal performance that barely rises above speaking volume, it achieves an emotional impact that belies its minimal arrangement.\n\nThe album's centre — tracks five through seven — represents its most ambitious section: a three-part suite that traces a relationship from first meeting to final goodbye. The songwriting here is at its most literary, with images that linger long after the music stops.\n\nThe closing track, which runs over nine minutes, has been the subject of the most debate. It's a sprawling, restless piece that refuses easy resolution — a fitting conclusion to an album that consistently challenges its audience.\n\nCritics have been nearly unanimous in their praise. The album currently holds a score of 96 on review aggregator sites, making it the highest-rated release of the year.",
